        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><strong>Opioid Prescription Verification Act of 2021</strong></p> <p>This bill modifies overdose prevention activities carried out by the Department of Health and Human Services (HHS) and the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC).</p> <p>Specifically, HHS must update pharmacist training materials to include information about how to verify the identity of individuals who pick up prescribed medications.</p> <p>In addition, the CDC may give preference, in awarding grants for overdose prevention, to states that</p> <ul> <li>maintain a prescription drug monitoring program that mandates the collection of specified information, and </li> <li>require dispensers of certain potentially addictive drugs to verify the identity of individuals who pick up prescribed medications. </li> </ul>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
      <summary>
