        <updateDate>2021-12-07T17:04:09Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><strong>Opioid Prescription Verification Act of 2021</strong></p> <p>This bill modifies overdose prevention activities carried out by the Department of Health and Human Services (HHS) and the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC).</p> <p>Specifically, HHS must update pharmacist training materials to include information about how to verify the identity of patients who are prescribed medications.</p> <p>In addition, the CDC may give preference, in awarding grants for overdose prevention, to states that</p> <ul> <li>maintain a prescription drug monitoring program that mandates the collection of specified information,</li> <li>require prescribers of certain potentially addictive medications to issue prescriptions electronically (subject to some exceptions), and</li> <li>require dispensers of certain potentially addictive medications to enter particular information about the purchase of such medications into their state's prescription drug monitoring program.</li> </ul>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
